ber-tomb at Milatos. II. The Royal Tomb at Isopata | series=Archaeologia 59 (1905) pages 391\u2013562| location=London | publisher=B. Quaritch | year=1906B | url=https://archive.org/stream/prehistorictombs00evan#page/n3/mode/2up}}\n* {{cite book | ref=harv | first=Arthur John | last=Evans | author-mask=2 | title=Scripta Minoa: The Written Documents of Minoan Crete: with Special Reference to the Archives of Knossos | volume=Volume I: The Hieroglyphic and Primitive Linear Classes: with an account of the discovery of the pre-Phoenician scripts, their place in the Minoan story and their Mediterranean relatives: with plates, tables and figures in the text | location=Oxford | publisher=Clarendon Press | year=1909 | url=https://archive.org/stream/scriptaminoawrit01evanuoft#page/n5/mode/2up}}\n* {{cite journal | ref=harv | first=Arthur John | last=Evans | author-mask=2 | title=The Minoan and Mycenaean Element in Hellenic Life | journal=The Journal of Hellenic Studies | volume=32 | pages=277\u2013287 | url=https://archive.org/stream/journalofhelleni32sociuoft#page/276/mode/2up/search/Minoan | year=1912 | doi=10.2307/624176| jstor=624176 }}\n* {{cite journal | ref=harv | first=Arthur John | last=Evans | author-mask=2 | title=The 'Tomb of the Double Axes' and Associated Group, and the Pillar Rooms and Ritual Vessels of the 'Little Palace' at Knossos | journal=Archaeologia | volume=65 | pages=1\u201394 | year=1914 | url=http://digi.ub.uni-heidelberg.de/diglit/evans1914/0021?sid=4d5171c9f3498b7399864c2eb2aac0e8 | doi=10.1017/s0261340900010833}}\n* {{cite book | ref=harv | first=Arthur John | last=Evans | author-mask=2 | title=The Palace of Minos (PM): a comparative account of the successive stages of the early Cretan civilization as illustrated by the discoveries at Knossos | location=London | publisher=MacMillan and Co}}\n** {{cite book | ref=harv | first=Arthur John | last=Evans | author-mask=2 | title=PM | year=1921 | volume=Volume I: The Neolithic and Early and Middle Minoan